18/01/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Nikola Kljusev, the first prime minister of independent Macedonia, died late Wednesday (January 16th) at the age of 80.
Kljusev was also a former defence minister and a member of Macedonia's Academy of Science and Arts.
He is being buried on Friday, as the country observes a day of mourning.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 18/01/08;
Mia, Makfax, MRT - 17/01/08)
